DAYO was created to help people interact and make the world a more open and inclusive place. To put it another way, we want to create a world where everybody can fit in wherever. We are a trust-based community. To win your trust, we must be transparent about how we utilize your information and preserve your human right to privacy.
This Privacy Policy explains how DAYO, and its affiliates handle personal information collected via the DAYO Platform. The extra privacy pages listed below may apply to you depending on where you live and what you do on the DAYO Platform. Please click on the links provided and read the extra information about how we process personal information for locations and services.

1. DEFINITIONS
The definition of undefined terms in this Privacy Policy is the same as in our Terms of Service (“Terms”).
2. INFORMATION ABOUT PERSONAL IDENTIFICATION OUR COLLECTION
2.1 Data required to use the DAYO Platform
•	When you use the DAYO Platform, we collect personal information about you. We may not be able to offer you with all the services you have requested without it. Contact details, account information, and profile information are all included. Your first and last names, phone number, postal address, email address, date of birth, and profile photo, to name a few, will all be determined by the services you utilize.
•	Verification of identity and payment information. For example, photographs of your government-issued ID (as permitted by applicable legislation), your ID number or other verification information, and information about your bank account or payment account.
2.2 Information you voluntarily provide to us
•	You have the option of providing us with extra personal data. Additional Profile Area may be included in this information. Gender, preferred language(s), city, and personal description are just a few examples. Some of this information is part of your public profile page and will be publicly viewable, as determined in your account preferences.
•	Contact Information from the Address Book. You can import or manually enter contacts into your address book.
•	Additional data. When you fill out a form, update your account information, react to surveys, post to community forums, participate in promotions, connect with our customer service team and other Members, or share your experience with us, we collect information from you. If you want to share your health information with us, this may include it.




2.3 Data Collected Automatically Through the DAYO Platform and Our Payment Services
We automatically collect personal information when you use the DAYO Platform and Payment Services. This data could include the following:
•	Information about how to use it. Such is the pages or material you read, listing searches, reservations you've made, and other DAYO Platform actions.
•	Data from the logs and information about the device. Such as your IP address, access dates and times, hardware and software information, device information, device event information, unique identifiers, crash data, cookie data, and the pages you've visited or engaged with before or after using the DAYO Platform. Even if you haven't registered a DAYO account or logged in, we may collect this information.
•	Information on Payment Transactions. Such as the payment instrument used, the date and time of the transaction, the amount paid, the payment instrument's expiration date and billing postcode, PayPal's email address, your address, and other transaction-related information.
3. HOW DO WE USE THE DATA WE COLLECT?
3.1 Make the DAYO platform available, improve it, and expand it. We use personal information to: 
•	enable you to access the DAYO Platform and make and receive payments, enable you to communicate with other Members, 
•	perform analytics, debug, and conduct research, 
•	provide customer service, 
•	Messages, updates, security alerts, and account notifications will be sent to you.
•	If you give us information about your contacts, such as friends or co-travelers, we may use it to: I facilitate your referral invitations, (ii) share your trip details and facilitate trip planning, (iii) detect and prevent fraud, and (iv) facilitate your requests or for any other reason you authorize.
•	based on your interactions with the DAYO Platform, your search and booking history, your profile information and preferences, and other content you submit, personalize, and customize your experience, and
•	allow you to use our business products.
3.2 Establish and maintain a more trustworthy and secure environment. We utilize personal information for the following purposes:
•	detect and prevent fraud, spam, misuse, security and safety incidents, and other potentially hazardous behavior
•	validate or authenticate the information you've provided,
•	carry out checks against databases and other sources of information, such as background or police checks,
•	Protect the health and well-being of our Guests, Hosts, Hosts' staff, and members of the public by adhering to our legal requirements.
•	resolving conflicts with our members.

3.3 Provide, personalize, measure, and improve our marketing and advertising. Personal information may be used for the following purposes:
•	send you promotional messages, marketing, advertising, and other information based on your preferences and through social media platforms,
•	improve our advertising by personalizing, measuring, and customizing it
•	analyze your preferences and attributes to send you promotional messages, marketing, advertising, and other material that we believe may be of interest to you, and
•	invite you to relevant events and opportunities.
3.4 Make payment services available. To enable or permit third parties to use Payment Services, personal information is used:
•	Money laundering, fraud, misuse, and security events must all be detected and prevented.
•	Observe all legal requirements (such as anti-money laundering regulations).
•	Make sure that the Payment Terms and other payment regulations are followed.
•	Send you promotional communications, marketing, advertising, and other material that may be of interest to you depending on your preferences if you give us your permission.
•	Payment Services should be provided and improved.
4. RIGHTS OF THE CLIENT
In accordance with relevant law, you may exercise any of the rights indicated in this section. For more information about data subject rights requests and how to make one, go to this page. Please be aware that we may need to verify your identification and request before proceeding with your request.
4.1 Information Management
•	Some of your personal information can be seen and updated through your Account settings. You can update your preferences and unlink from a third-party service, such as Google or PayPal, under your DAYO Account settings. It is your responsibility to keep your personal information current.
4.2 Data Portability and Access
•	In some jurisdictions, applicable law may give you the right to request specific copies of your personal information or information about how we handle your personal information, as well as to request copies of personal information you've provided to us in a structured, commonly used, and machine-readable format, and/or to have this information transmitted to another service provider (where technically feasible).
5. SECURITY
While no company can guarantee 100% security, we are constantly adding and updating administrative, technical, and physical security measures to help safeguard your data from unauthorized access, loss, destruction, or alteration.


6. MODIFICATIONS TO THE PRIVACY POLICY
We retain the right, in line with current law, to change this Privacy Policy at any time. We will post the amended Privacy Policy if we do so. If there are any major changes, we will notify you by email at least thirty (30) days before the change becomes effective. You have the option to deactivate your Account if you disagree with the updated Privacy Policy. Your continued access to or use of the DAYO Platform will be subject to the updated Privacy Policy if you do not cancel your Account before the date the revised Privacy Policy becomes effective.
7. CONTACT INFORMATION AND RESPONSIBLE DAYO ENTITIES
If you have any questions or complaints about this Privacy Policy or DAYO's handling of personal information, please contact DAYO, Brgy. Poblacion, City of San Jose Del Monte, Bulacan; (ii) for payments-related issues, please use the contact information provided in the Payments Terms of Service page; and (iii) if you live outside of San Jose Del Monte, please contact DAYO, Brgy. Poblacion, City of San Jose Del Monte, Bulacan
